    {
      "id": "cultural_w2",
      "type": "cultural_note",
      "title": "Kulturelt hjørne — Cultural Corner",
      "heading": "Numbers and the Danish phone system",
      "content": "Danish phone numbers are always eight digits long and written in pairs: 71 23 45 67. Danes almost always give their number in pairs rather than individually. You will also notice that Danish numbers above 20 follow a very different pattern — 'halvtreds' (50) literally means 'half of three times twenty', a remnant of an old vigesimal (base-20) counting system. For now, numbers 0–20 are your priority, but do not be surprised when you hear 'halvtreds' and it means fifty!"
    }
